Write a JavaScript function called classifyChild(data) that takes:
{ age_months, weight_kg, height_cm, muac_cm }

And returns a classification object:
{
  status: "SAM" | "MAM" | "Normal" | "At-Risk",
  color: "red" | "orange" | "yellow" | "green",
  wfa_zscore: number,
  hfa_zscore: number,
  recommendation: string,
  urgency: "immediate" | "monitor" | "routine"
}

Use WHO child growth standard z-score approximations:
- SAM: MUAC < 11.5cm OR WFA z-score < -3
- MAM: MUAC 11.5-12.5cm OR WFA z-score -3 to -2  
- At-Risk: MUAC 12.5-13.5cm OR WFA z-score -2 to -1.5
- Normal: everything else

Add realistic recommendation messages for each status.
Export the function. Add JSDoc comments.